13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 11 O.S. 2021, Section 14-110, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 14-110. When a municipality has compiled and published
17 its permanent volume or biennial supplement of penal ordinances, the
18 governing body of the municipality shall adopt a resolution
19 notifying the public of the publication. A copy of the resolution
20 shall be filed in the office of the county clerk in each county in
21 which the municipality is located. The county clerk shall assign
22 the filed resolution a book and page number. At least one copy of
23 the permanent volume and each biennial supplement shall be deposited
24 free of cost by the municipality in the county law library of each
